x in Russia|2019 JGP Russia]]\n|SP score= 68.07\n|SP date= [[2019\u201320 Grand Prix of Figure Skating Final|2019-20 JGP Final]]\n|FS score= 131.75\n|FS date= [[ISU Junior Grand Prix in Russia|2019 JGP Russia]]\n}}\n\n'''Viktoria Borisovna Vasilieva''' (born 25 November 2003) is a Russian [[figure skater]]. On the junior level, she is the 2018 [[Inge Solar Memorial - Alpen Trophy|Alpen Trophy]] champion, the 2018 [[ISU Junior Grand Prix in the Czech Republic|Junior Grand Prix Czech Republic]] bronze medalist and the 2019 [[ISU Junior Grand Prix in Russia|Junior Grand Prix Russia]] bronze medalist.<ref name=\"ISU-VV\" />\n\n==Results==\n{|  class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: #ffdead; \" colspan=4 align=center | International<ref name=ISU-VV>{{cite web |url= http://www.isuresults.com/bios/isufs_cr_00102761.htm |title= Viktoria VASILIEVA |publisher= International Skating Union }}</ref>\n|-\n! Event\n! [[2017\u201318 figure skating season|17\u201318]]\n! [[2018\u201319 figure skating season|18\u201319]]\n! [[2019\u201320 figure skating season|19\u201320]]\n|-\n| align=left | [[Winter Youth Olympics|Youth Olympics]] || || || WD\n|-\n| align=left | {{small|JGP}} [[ISU Junior Grand Prix Final|Final]] || || || 6th\n|-\n| align=left | {{small|JGP}} [[ISU Junior Grand Prix in the Czech Republic|Czech Republic]] || || bgcolor=cc9966 | 3rd ||  \n|-\n| align=left | {{small|JGP}} [[ISU Junior Grand Prix in Poland|Poland]] || || || bgcolor=silver | 2nd\n|-\n| align=left | {{small|JGP}} [[ISU Junior Grand Prix in Russia|Russia]] || || || bgcolor=cc9966 | 3rd \n|-\n| align=left | [[Inge Solar Memorial - Alpen Trophy|Alpen Trophy]] || ||bgcolor=gold | 1st J || \n|-\n| align=left | [[Ice Star]] || bgcolor=cc9966 | 3rd J || ||  \n|-\n! style=\"background-color: #ffdead; \" colspan=4 align=center | National \n|-\n| align=left | [[Russian Figure Skating Championships|Russian Champ.]] || || 11th || WD\n|-\n| align=left | [[Russian Junior Figur