.com#Newspapers.com|Newspapers.com]]|ref=harv}} {{subscription required}}\n* {{cite journal|volume=17|issue=10|pages=133|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XBJLecfe-rcC&pg=PA133#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Show Us Your Hits|last=Clover|first=Joshua|date=October 2001|journal=[[Spin&nbsp;(magazine)|Spin]]|url-status=live|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/367066600/|url-access=subscription|title=CDs by Aaliyah, Craig David, Foxy Brown and Perry Farrell|last=Davis|first=Latrice|date=July 29, 2001|work=[[The Herald-Palladium]]|page=18|access-date=December 1, 2019|location=|via=[[Ancestry.com#Newspapers.com|Newspapers.com]]|ref=harv}} {{subscription required}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Esposito|first1=Jennifer|last2=Love|first2=Bettina|chapter=More Than A Video Ho: Hip Hop as a Site of Sex Education about Girls\u2019 Sexual Desires|chapter-url=https://www.google.com/books/edition/The_Corporate_Assault_on_Youth/hiJXTlFJ3SwC?hl=en&gbpv=1&dq=%22More+Than+A+Video+Ho:+Hip+Hop+as+a+Site+of+Sex+Education+about+Girls%E2%80%99+Sexual+Desires%22&pg=PA27|title=The Corporate Assault on Youth:&nbsp;Commercialism, Exploitation, and the End of Innocence |editor-last1 =Boyles |editor-first1 = Deron|year = 2008|page= 27\u201350 |publisher =[[Peter Lang (publisher)|Peter Lang]] |location =|isbn = 9781433100840 |ref = harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Faluyi|first1=Doyinsola|title=An Exploration into the Objectification of Self in Female Hip-Hop Culture as a Form of Misogyny or Empowerment|journal=Journal of Promotional Communications|volume=3|issue=3|year=2015|publisher=[[Bournemouth University]]|page=446\u2013464|url=https://promotionalcommunications.org/index.php/pc/article/view/68/80|doi=|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|volume=113|issue=34|pages=18|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_hMEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA18#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=R&B|last=Finan|first=Colin|date=August 25, 2001|journal=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191202235610/https://books.google.com/books?id=_hMEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA18#v=onepage&q&f=false|archivedate=December 2, 2019|url-status=live|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Fonseca|first1=Anthony J.|title=Listen to Rap! Exploring a Musical Genre|year=2019|publisher=[[ABC-CLIO]]|location=|isbn=9781440865671|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o6KsDwAAQBAJ|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sGHYVTJadwE|title=Foxy Brown - Tables Will Turn ft. Baby Cham|date=June 16, 2009|publisher=[[YouTube]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170809021324/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sGHYVTJadwE|archivedate=August 9, 2017|url-status=live|ref={{sfnref|YouTube}}}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://theboombox.com/deaf-history-month-2012-foxy-brown/|title=Deaf History Month 2012: Foxy Brown Suffers Loss, Bounces Back Video|last=Graham|first=Nadine|date=March 13, 2012|work=[[The Boombox]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309134926/http://theboombox.com/deaf-history-month-2012-foxy-brown/|archivedate=March 9, 2017|url-status=live|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|editor-last1=Malewski|editor-first1=Erik|title=Curriculum Studies Handbook - The Next Moment|chapter=(A) Troubling Curriculum: Public Pedagogies of Black Women Rappers|author-last1=Guillory|author-first1=Nichole A.|url=https://www.google.com/books/edition/Curriculum_Studies_Handbook_The_Next_Mom/hGeRAgAAQBAJ|year=2009|publisher=[[Taylor & Francis]]|location=|isbn=9781135857653|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Hall|first=Rashaun|date=July 28, 2001|title=Reviews & Previews|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-RMEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA22#v=onepage&q&f=false|url-status=live|journal=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|volume=113|issue=30|pages=22|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191202235728/https://books.google.com/books?id=-RMEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA22#v=onepage&q&f=false|archivedate=December 2, 2019|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/foxy-brown/chart-history/r-b-hip-hop-songs/song/406810|title=Hot 